items.name: Mason Jar Quinoa Salad

ingredients.name: 1 pinch salt and pepper, to taste
2 cups (370g) cooked quinoa (certified gluten-free if necessary)
1 cup (195g) black beans (certified gluten-free if necessary)

items.directions: To make the dressing, place all ingredients for the salad dressing into a small food processor and process until smooth.\n\nAdd 3 tablespoons of salad dressing to the mason jar base. Then add the following ingredients in this order: 1 cup spinach, 1/4 cup tomatoes, 1/2 cup cooked quinoa, 1/4 cup black beans, 1/4 cup corn and 1/2 avocado (diced).

items.name: Protein Oats
items.directions:
Add rolled oats, minced banana, cinnamon, and 1 cup of milk (if choosing a non-dairy milk try to select one high in protein such as soy, oat or pea) and a dash of salt to a pot. Cook over medium to high heat until the liquid has been absorbed (6-8 min).

Then add your egg whites and stir constantly to prevent eggs from scrambling. This should take about two minutes and you should be left with fluffy oats.

Drizzle with nut butter and enjoy!

items.name: Slow Cooker Chicken Tortilla Soup
items.directions: Place the chicken, broth, black beans and salsa in a slow cooker. Cook on low for 8 hours or high for 4 hours. Remove chicken and shred, then return to soup. Spoon soup into bowls, topping with avocado and tortilla chips.

items.name: Low Sugar Acai Bowl

ingredients.name: 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk, or milk of your choice/water

items.directions:
Add all ingredients into your blender including 1 acai packet, ½ of a frozen banana, ½ C unsweetened vanilla almond milk (or your choice of milk, water or other non-dairy milk), and ½ scoop of protein powder.

Blend until smooth and to your desired consistency.

Drizzle with 1 tbsp of nut butter and your choice of berries.

items.name: Berries and Cream
items.directions: Add mixed berries to a bowl and top with whipped cream and sprinkles!

items.name: Gnocchi-Cauliflower Skillet Casserole
items.directions:
Heat a 10-inch cast-iron or other ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Remove sausage from casings and crumble into the pan. Cook until browned, stirring to crumble, about 5 minutes.

Add cauliflower and 1/2 cup (118ml) water; cover, reduce heat to medium, and cook for 5 minutes. Stir in marinara sauce and gnocchi; cover, reduce heat to medium-low, and cook until cauliflower and gnocchi are tender, about 6 minutes.

Preheat the broiler to high. Uncover the pan, and sprinkle evenly with cheese. Broil until the cheese melts, 1–2 minutes.

items.name: High-Protein Chicken Salad

ingredients.name: 1 pound cooked chicken breast or rotisserie chicken, shredded (about 4 cups)

semantics.food: cooked chicken breast or rotisserie chicken

ingredients.name: 2/3 cup plain 2% fat Greek yogurt (certified gluten-free if necessary

semantics.food: plain 2% fat Greek yogurt (certified gluten-free if necessary

ingredients.name: 1 pinch salt and pepper, to taste
12 sliced 100% whole grain bread (about 100 calories each)

items.directions: In a large bowl, combine shredded chicken, red onion, apple, grapes, Greek yogurt, lemon juice, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Mix until well combined.\n\nUsing a 3/4 cup measuring scoop, portion out the chicken salad. Serve with a lettuce leaf and 2 slices of 100% whole grain bread.

items.name: Yogurt and Nut Butter

ingredients.name: 1/4 cup unsweetened goji berries, or dried fruit of your choice

semantics.preparation_notes: or dried fruit of your choice

items.directions: Add your yogurt to a bowl and top with nut butter and dried fruit. Enjoy!

items.name: Sweet and Salty Popcorn
items.directions: Mix together and enjoy!

items.name: Tuna or Turkey Melt Sandwich

ingredients.name: 2 slices 100% whole wheat bread, lightly toasted
1 pinch salt and pepper, to taste

items.directions:
Pre toast bread until lightly toasted. 

Mix 1 4 oz can of drained tuna with mustard (1 tbsp or to taste), salt, pepper and relish (about 2 tbsp). Put 2 slices of toast in the oven layering the tuna mixture, tomato, and avocado with one slice of cheese on top. When the cheese is melted add the spinach and enjoy!

Optional- add a drizzle of olive oil and balsamic to kick up the flavor! Not a tuna lover? Try turkey instead of the tuna mixture.

items.name: Double-Chocolate Zucchini Bread

ingredients.name: 1/3 cup  mild olive oil or canola oil

semantics.food: mild olive oil or canola oil

ingredients.name: 2 cups  zucchini , grated (from one large 9-ounce zucchini)

items.directions:
Preheat oven to 350°F (178°C). Coat a 9-by-5-inch (23-by-13cm) loaf pan or an 8-inch (20cm) square baking pan with cooking spray. Set aside. Sift the flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt into a large bowl.

In another bowl, whisk together the coconut sugar, oil, yogurt, maple syrup, eggs and extract. Add the wet ingredients to the flour mixture and stir until just combined (with a few traces of flour still present). Add the zucchini and chocolate chips and stir to combine. The batter will be quite thick.

Spoon the batter into the prepared baking pan and flatten the top with a rubber spatula. Bake until a toothpick inserted into the center of the bread comes out clean, about 45 minutes for a loaf pan and 30 minutes for an 8-inch square pan. Cool in the pan for 10 minutes. Run a knife around the edges of the pan and invert onto a cooling rack. Wrap leftovers tightly and store at room temperature for up to four days.

items.name: Instant Pot Rotini With Chicken and Bell Peppers

ingredients.name: 3 cup low-sodium chicken, or vegetable broth
1/4 cup oil-packed sun-dried tomatoes, drained and chopped
1 pinch salt and pepper, to taste
1 small red bell pepper, thinly sliced

items.directions:
In the pot of an electric pressure cooker, whisk together the broth and tomato paste until the tomato paste is dissolved. Add the pasta, sun-dried tomatoes, olive oil, rosemary, 1/4 teaspoon salt and several grinds of pepper. Stir to combine. Place the bell peppers on top of the pasta. Season the chicken with the garlic seasoning and place on top of the pasta mixture, do not stir.

Lock on the lid, select the Manual/Pressure Cook function. Adjust to high pressure and set timer for 4 minutes. Make sure the steam valve is in the “sealing” position.

When the cooking time is up, carefully quick-release the pressure.

Unlock the lid and transfer the chicken to a clean cutting board. Slice the meat into bite-size pieces and return them to the pot. Add the spinach and cheese and stir to wilt the spinach. Serve immediately.

items.name: Breakfast Tacos

ingredients.name: 1/4 medium avocado, sliced, 2-3 thin slices per taco

items.directions:
Use an olive oil spray to line your pan. Scramble your eggs in a separate dish and add them to your pan over medium heat. 

Measure out your beans and feta and mince your spinach. Add all ingredients to the eggs while they are still runny.

Use a tortilla warmer to heat your tortillas or cook them on the stove top. Once your eggs are cooked, add the mixture to your tortillas and top with sliced avocado and your choice of salsa or hot sauce.

items.name: Slow Cooker Irish Beef Stew

ingredients.name: 2 medium Russet potatoes , peeled and chopped

items.directions:
Sprinkle stew meat with salt and toss till well combined. Using a fork, prick the meat in multiple places to tenderize. Cover and refrigerate for at least an hour, but ideally refrigerate overnight.

Toss the meat with flour. Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Add oil and then sear meat until browned on the outside.

While meat is browning, mix together tomato paste, soy sauce, beef stock (use more if you like it more soupy than stewy) and Guinness & red wine (if using) in slow cooker.

Transfer meat (browned or not) to slow cooker. Add garlic, onions, carrots, potatoes, bay leaves, and black pepper.

Cook on low for 6 to 7 hours or high for 3 to 4 until meat is falling apart and tender.

If using peas, microwave for ~1 minute and then fold them into stew.

Remove bay leaves. Season to taste with salt and pepper and enjoy!

items.name: 5-Ingredient Chocolate Peanut Butter Cups

ingredients.name: 1/3 cup (85g) all-natural peanut butter, or nut butter of your choice

semantics.food: all-natural peanut butter, or nut butter of your choice

ingredients.name: 1 tablespoon plain or vanilla collagen peptide powder

semantics.food: plain or vanilla collagen peptide powder

items.directions:
Line a 12-well muffin tin with paper liners and set aside. In a small bowl combine the peanut butter, collagen powder, honey and vanilla, stirring until smooth. Set aside in the refrigerator.

Place the chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl and heat on 60% power in 1-minute increments, stirring between cooking times, until all the chocolate has melted, 3–4 minutes. Alternatively, melt the chocolate in a metal bowl set over a pot with a few inches of simmering water on the stove, stirring until smooth. (Be sure not to get any steam or water in the chocolate or it will seize.)

Spoon about 1 teaspoon of the chocolate into the paper liners, spreading the chocolate to the edges. Using a 1/2 teaspoon measure, put a heaping spoonful of the peanut butter mixture in the center of each muffin cup. Spoon the remaining chocolate over the peanut butter, about 2 teaspoons per muffin cup.

Refrigerate until the chocolate is set, about 4 hours. Remove the peanut butter cups (still in their liners) from the muffin tin and store in the refrigerator in an airtight container for up to two weeks.

items.name: Baked Egg Cups with Garlic Toast

ingredients.name: 1/2 cup (70 grams) asparagus, trimmed and chopped
1 clove garlic, peeled and sliced in half lengthwise

semantics.preparation_notes: peeled and sliced in half lengthwise

ingredients.name: 1 piece fruit, of your choice to eat on the side

semantics.preparation_notes: of your choice to eat on the side

items.directions:
Arrange a rack in center of oven and preheat to 350°F (177°C). Fill a 9-inch square baking pan halfway with very hot water. Butter 4 (6-ounce) ramekins with 1 teaspoon butter each. Set aside.

In a large skillet on medium high, heat remaining 2 teaspoons butter until foamy. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring frequently, until golden brown, about 4 minutes. Divide mushrooms evenly among ramekins. Top with asparagus and half and half, dividing evenly. Crack 1 egg into each ramekin and top with cheese. Season with salt and pepper.

Set ramekins into prepared pan and carefully transfer to oven. Bake until whites are set and yolks are still slightly runny, 15 to 18 minutes. Meanwhile, rub cut side of garlic over 1 side of each bread slice, and toast until golden. Cut into triangles and serve with egg cups.

items.name: Build Your Own Salad

ingredients.name: 2 cups greens (spinach, kale, romaine, or a mixture)

semantics.food: greens (spinach, kale, romaine, or a mixture)

ingredients.name: 3 ounces  protein (chicken, shrimp, steak, 1 egg, tofu ect.)

semantics.food: protein (chicken, shrimp, steak, 1 egg, tofu ect.)

ingredients.name: 1 cup vegetable, fruit or a mixture
2 tablespoons crumbled cheese such as feta, blue cheese, goat cheese ect.

semantics.food: crumbled cheese such as feta, blue cheese, goat cheese ect.

ingredients.name: 2 tablespoons nuts, seeds, roasted chickpeas,  crispy quinoa or croutons , (1/4 cup if you choose croutons)

semantics.food: nuts, seeds, roasted chickpeas,  crispy quinoa or croutons

items.directions: Cook your protein (if necessary) and layer ingredients starting with your greens. Drizzle olive oil and vinegar on top (or your chosen dressing) and enjoy!

items.name: Mix and Match Dinner with Chicken, Fish, or Beef

ingredients.name: 4 ounces chicken breast, salmon, fish, or steak

semantics.food: chicken breast, salmon, fish, or steak

ingredients.name: 1/16 cup cooked quinoa, rice, farro, or roasted sweet potato

semantics.food: cooked quinoa, rice, farro, or roasted sweet potato

ingredients.name: 1/16 cup chopped vegetable of your choice

items.directions:
Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.

Season the protein with salt, pepper, and spices of your choice (paprika and garlic powder recommended).

Roast protein in the oven until fully cooked (cooking time will depend on the type of protein used).

While protein is roasting, prepare the grain.

Sauce the vegetables in olive oil in a frying pan over medium heat.

items.name: Banana Bread Overnight Oats
items.directions: Mash half of the banana in a jar, container, or bowl. Next, add the oats, yogurt, milk, chia seeds, cinnamon and stir to combine. Refrigerate overnight. The next morning, top with pecans and the remaining 1/2 banana and enjoy. Optional: drizzle maple syrup or honey on top for sweetness.

items.name: Protein Toast

ingredients.name: 1 whole hard boiled egg, sliced in half

items.directions: Toast your bread, layer your avocado and boil egg on top and season to your liking.

items.name: Build Your Own Avocado Toast

ingredients.name: 1 large slice of whole grain toast
1 protein of your choice- eggs, grated tofu, smoked salmon or pepitas

semantics.food: of your choice- eggs, grated tofu, smoked salmon or pepitas

ingredients.name: 1/2 cup veggies of your choice- spinach, tomato, onions, cucumber, microgreens ect.

semantics.food: veggies of your choice- spinach, tomato, onions, cucumber, microgreens ect.

ingredients.name: 1 pinch everything seasoning, to your taste

items.directions:
Toast your bread and add your avocado and everything seasoning. 

Choose your veggies, aim for about ½ C but the more the better!

Then top it off with your favorite protein- some great options are 1 hard boiled egg, a scrambled egg, 2 oz of smoked salmon, 3 oz of grated and seasoned tofu or ¼ C pepitas.

items.name: Greek Yogurt and Fruit

ingredients.name: 1/2 cup berries, or other chopped fruit

items.directions: Use: Small snack 1-2 hours before a 30-45min cardio or strength workout.

items.name: Quinoa Edamame Egg Muffins
items.directions:
Preheat the oven to 350ºF (177ºC). Line eight cups in a muffin pan with paper liners and set aside.

In a small pot, bring 1/2 cup water to a boil. Add the quinoa, cover tightly and reduce the heat to low. Cook for 14 minutes, then remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes. The water should all be absorbed; let cool.

In a large bowl, combine the eggs, egg whites and whisk until mixed. Add the yogurt and parmesan and whisk until smooth. Stir in the parsley, edamame and cooked quinoa.

Divide the egg mixture between the prepared muffin cups, filling almost to the top.

Bake for 30 minutes, until puffed and firm to the touch. Cool in pan on a rack. Serve warm. To save for the week, let cool completely to room temperature before transferring to a storage container and covering tightly. Refrigerate for up to four days.

items.name: Roasted Chickpeas
items.directions: Preheat your oven to 375 degrees F. Dry the chickpeas well and toss them well with oil and sea salt. Roast for 20-30 minutes or until crispy.

items.name: Maple Cinnamon Breakfast Trail Mix
items.directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Combine almonds, cashews, pistachios and coconut flakes in a mixing bowl with maple syrup, cinnamon, vanilla and sea salt. Toss to combine.\n\nSpread nut mixture onto a baking sheet, and bake for about 10 –12 minutes, until nuts are fragrant and golden brown. Remove from oven, and allow nuts to cool. Toss with dried berries, and enjoy (1/4 C is equal to 1 serving). Store leftover mix in a covered storage container for up to a week.

items.name: Chicken and Zucchini Enchiladas

ingredients.name: 1 medium zucchini, shredded and excess liquid squeezed out

semantics.preparation_notes: shredded and excess liquid squeezed out

ingredients.name: 1 large ear corn, shucked and kernels cut from the cob

semantics.preparation_notes: shucked and kernels cut from the cob

ingredients.name: 1 cup canned low-sodium black beans, rinsed and drained
1 pinch  salt and pepper, to taste
3 cups (365g) packed shredded chicken or 1/2 of a rotisserie chicken

semantics.food: packed shredded chicken or 1/2 of a rotisserie chicken

items.directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F (205°C). In a large bowl, combine the chicken, zucchini, corn, black beans, cilantro, cumin, 1/2 cup of tomatillo salsa, 1/2 cup of Greek yogurt and 1/2 the cotija cheese. Season with salt and pepper. Spread 1 cup of the tomatillo salsa in the bottom of a 9-by-13-inch baking dish. Working with one tortilla at a time, spread a scant 1/2-cup of the chicken filling down the middle of a tortilla and roll it up like a cigar. Place the enchilada seam-side down in the baking dish. Repeat with the remaining tortillas and filling. Spread the remaining 1-cup of tomatillo salsa over the top of the enchiladas and sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup of cotija cheese. Bake until bubbling and beginning to brown, about 20 minutes. Let cool slightly. The enchilada filling can be refrigerated overnight.\n\nMeanwhile, in a small bowl, whisk the remaining 1/2 cup of Greek yogurt with the 2 tablespoons lime juice. Season with salt and pepper. Drizzle the lime crema over the enchiladas and garnish with cilantro and chopped avocado. Serve with lime wedges and hot sauce.
